  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">People living in the remote areas of the Karamoja region are the poorest in Uganda facing long periods of food shortages due to extreme floods and droughts and cattle raiding. Even when the growing season is good lack of storage means food runs out before the next harvest and prices rise rapidly. Over the last two years a UK charity has worked with a locally based community enterprise to set up a food storage facility known as a Food Hub. This one food hub has benefitted over 1000 farmers and families through increased income and food security. This project aims to gather the information necessary to set up Food Hubs throughout the region.</narrative>
  </description>
